modules.description: Provides operations to traverse, modify, and analyze graph structures representing profiling data, including depth-first search, subgraph extraction, and node labeling. Works with node and graph types that encode hierarchical call relationships and metadata. Used to generate visualizations, filter unreachable nodes, and compute metrics like call intensity and depth.

Tracks code execution by measuring CPU cycles, applicative time, and memory allocation. It records these metrics in a callgraph structure during program runtime. Results can be printed to the console or exported as JSON for analysis.

provides graph traversal, modification, and analysis tools for profiling data, supporting depth-first search, subgraph extraction, and node labeling. It operates on graph and node types that represent hierarchical call relationships and metadata. Users can generate visualizations, filter unreachable nodes, and calculate metrics such as call intensity. It enables detailed analysis of program execution flow and performance characteristics.

Provides thread-safe access to landmark data through coordinated synchronization mechanisms. Exposes atomic operations for reading and updating landmarks, ensuring consistency across concurrent processes. Supports safe initialization and destruction of landmark resources. Can prevent race conditions when multiple threads modify shared landmark states.
